setRoot

public void setRoot(Node newRoot)
Set this node as the root of the tree. This will throw a RuntimeException if this tree already has a root, if the given node is a child or if the given node is already associated with a tree.

Parameters:
newRoot - the node to be set as the tree root

unsetRoot

Returns:
the root node that was removed

countNodes

public int countNodes(boolean includeInvisible)
Count the total amount of nodes in the tree. When includeInvisible is set to false, this method will not count nodes where isVisible() evaluates to false.

Parameters:
includeInvisible - whether to include hidden nodes or not
Returns:
the amount of nodes in the tree

nodeList

public Node[] nodeList(boolean includeInvisible)
Return an array with all the nodes in the tree. When includeInvisible is set to false, this method will not count nodes where isVisible() evaluates to false.

Parameters:
includeInvisible - whether to include hidden nodes or not
Returns:
an array containing all the nodes

nodesAtLevel

public Node[] nodesAtLevel(int level,
                           boolean includeInvisible)
Nodes at the specified level. This returns a list of all the nodes at a certain level. The root is at level 0, its children are at level 1, their children are at level 2 etcetera. When includeInvisible is set to false, this method will not count nodes where isVisible() evaluates to false.

Parameters:
includeInvisible - whether to include hidden nodes or not
Returns:
an array containing all the nodes at the specified level

countLevels

public int countLevels(boolean includeInvisible)
Count the maximum amount of levels in our tree. When includeInvisible is set to false, this method will not count nodes where isVisible() evaluates to false.

Parameters:
includeInvisible - whether to include hidden nodes or not
Returns:
the amount of levels in the tree

processTree

public void processTree(NodeProcessor nodeProcessor)
Iterate through the tree using a NodeProcessor. The root will be the first node to be processed, and parents will be processed before their children. Other than that, there should be no assumptions about the order in which nodes are processed.

Parameters:
nodeProcessor - the NodeProcessor instance to use

setTreeScene

public void setTreeScene(TreeScene set)
Attach this tree to a TreeScene object. This also handles decoupling from existing scene. Note that this does not automatically cause an update, so you can attach your own (non-default) components to Nodes before the update would attach defaults.

Parameters:
set - the TreeScene instance to attach this Tree to

getTreeScene

public TreeScene getTreeScene()
Get the TreeScene instance associated with this Tree.

Returns:
the TreeScene instance this Tree is attached to, or null if there is none

needsUpdate

public boolean needsUpdate()
Return whether this Tree needs an update. When the structure of the Tree changes, or when nodes are switched between hidden or visible, the Tree is invalidated. The invalidation is lifted when the system has finished a visual update.

Returns:
whether this tree needs an update or not
